  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0ba9\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1: 10 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bb2\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Stabbing in Canada: 10 dead",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "At least 10 people have died and 15 others have been injured in a stabbing attack in Canada's central Saskatchewan province yesterday.",
        "A series of stabbings were carried out in the James Smith Cree Nation, Weldon and Saskatoon in the province's Rajina city.",
        "Police said victims were found in 13 locations, including the James Smith Cree Nation and Weldon.",
        "Royal Canadian Mounted Police Assistant Commissioner Rhonda Blackmore said they are looking for two suspects in connection with the incident.",
        "Canadian police have released information about the suspects who carried out the attack. 31-year-old Damien Sanderson and 30-year-old Miles Sanderson have been warned. (a)"
      ],
